# Append-only JSONL ledgers (event log work/events/*.jsonl, usage work/usage/*.jsonl)
# are written by many branches + the hourly heartbeat's auto-commits to main. Without
# a union driver, every such append collides on merge and manufactures a false
# "CONFLICTING/undeliverable" PR on the JSONL alone (zero product-code conflict) —
# the TICKET-F110 class bug. `merge=union` makes git (and GitHub's merge button)
# auto-resolve these by keeping BOTH sides' lines, so these conflicts never need a
# human. Union is correct precisely because these files are append-only.
*.jsonl merge=union
